-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - July 28
-- 
-- Mon Jul 28, 2014 02:38AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, July 28 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The Bulgarian Socialist Party has nominated Sergei Stanishev for a second term in office as president of the Party of European Socialists (Trud, Standart, Presa, 24 Chasa). -- Opposition Reformist Bloc, a group of right-wing and centrist parties currently without representation in the parliament, will take part in the early election in October on its own and will not form a coalition with centre-right GERB party, Reformist Bloc's senior official Meglena Kuneva said (Presa, Trud, Monitor, 24 Chasa). -- The Bulgarian Association of Agricultural Producers has opposed plans of the government to impose a 300,000 euros ($402,900) cap on the annual amount of area-based direct payments (24 Chasa, Duma).